data.content:
Works. Here's the summary:

**Getting `JsonTypeInfo<T>` (strongly-typed)**
```csharp
JsonTypeInfo<Person> info =
    (JsonTypeInfo<Person>)options.GetTypeInfo(typeof(Person));
```
`GetTypeInfo(Type)` returns the non-generic base; cast it to `JsonTypeInfo<T>`.

**Probing without throwing**
```csharp
if (options.TryGetTypeInfo(typeof(Person), out JsonTypeInfo? info))
{
    // available – safe to cast to JsonTypeInfo<T>
}
else
{
    // not available – no exception
}
```
`TryGetTypeInfo` (available since .NET 9) returns `false` instead of throwing when the resolver can't produce metadata for the requested type.
